## CDS Design System Quick Reference
- Primary: #4b3fff (Blurple), Secondary: #546574 (Slate)
- Font: DM Sans, Heading weight: 600, Button weight: 500
- Border radius: 4px, Spacing: 4px grid
- Breakpoints: Desktop 1440, Tablet 768, Mobile 390

## Component Hierarchy
1. CDS components → 2. MUI with CDS theme → 3. Custom with CDS tokens

## Mandatory Rules
- CDSPageHeader on every page
- No hardcoded colors/spacing/font sizes — theme tokens only
- CDS supports **light + dark mode** (theme.palette.mode, shared/tokens/colors-dark.ts)
- Font is ALWAYS **DM Sans**
- Spacing ALWAYS on **4px grid**
- **Figma canvas safety**: NEVER delete/move existing top-level screen frames. Scan page first, place new screens to the RIGHT with 200px gap. (Inside a screen you're building, freely manage child elements.)
- **Global Navigation on EVERY screen**: Every screen MUST start with a `Global Navigation` instance (`layoutSizingHorizontal = 'FILL'`). Use the **suite-specific Product variant** when one exists (Procurement, B&P, Utility Billing, Asset Management, Agents Studio, Vendor Portal, Command Center); else use Default (key `c24369659d8f75ec3815d2d3ffb1342dd7e551b5`). All breakpoints. No exceptions.
- **Page Heading from library**: NEVER hand-build page headers. Always use the `Page Heading` component (set key `ed8d390034cdc9b76fc11e1e2647856ff734d33d`). Set `layoutSizingHorizontal = 'FILL'`, use `Small Screen: True` for tablet/mobile.
- **Content parity across breakpoints**: ALL breakpoints MUST contain the same data and content sections. Never drop, truncate, or omit content for smaller screens. Adapt the **layout** only.
- **Global Nav + Page Heading = mandatory on every screen**: No screen is complete without both.

## MUI Component Rules (CRITICAL)
Theme covers 70+ components with all semantic colors. Use props, not manual sx.

- **Typography**: `variant` + `color` — never manual fontSize/fontWeight/fontFamily
- **Button**: `variant` + `color` + `size` — never manual bgcolor/height/borderRadius
- **TextField**: `size` — theme handles typography, radius, focus. Use `slotProps` not `InputProps`.
- **Checkbox/Radio/Switch**: `color` + `size` + `FormControlLabel`
- **Alert**: `severity` + optional `variant="filled"/"outlined"`
- **Chip**: `color` + `size` + optional `variant="outlined"`. Use status-to-color mapping: `Record<string, 'info' | 'success' | 'warning' | 'error' | 'default'>`
- **Card**: `variant="outlined"` for dashboard sections. Use subcomponents as-is.
- **Link**: `variant` + `color` + `underline="hover"` for clickable text. Never Typography with onClick.
- **Dialog/Accordion**: use subcomponents as-is
- Page components = **ZERO direct token imports**. Use palette paths only.
- sx for **layout only**: display, flex, gap, p/m, width, position, textAlign
- **Charts**: recharts (simple) + Highcharts (gantt, heatmap, treemap). Both use `capitalDesignTokens` + `useTheme()`.
- **Forms**: react-hook-form + yup (typed schemas, field/form errors, unsaved guard).
- **State**: zustand for global state (dashboard, preferences, theme).
- **Rich text**: TipTap for description/notes fields (CDS-styled toolbar).
- **`import type`**: ALWAYS for type-only imports. Missing this = blank page, zero console errors.

